parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Totally Integrated Power Module (TIPM) can cause a range of electrical system malfunctions, including horn honking, wiper activation, washer fluid spraying, and door lock malfunction, which can lead to accidents, injuries, or property damage.
The failure of the sliding door can cause injuries or fatalities, especially if the door opens or closes unexpectedly while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: door flying open while in motion
and electrical fire in the door.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while in motion, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Key falling out of the ignition switch

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear and failure can lead to reduced stopping power, increased stopping distances, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noises when applying the brakes
brake pedal feels soft or spongy
brake pads and rotors need to be replaced frequently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped brake rotors can cause the brakes to vibrate or pulsate, leading to reduced stopping power and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: brake pedal feels soft or spongy
unusual noises when applying the brakes.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system issues can cause various problems, including failure of the anti-lock braking system (ABS), loss of power steering, and instrument panel failures.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Acceleration and stopping issues can cause loss of control and potentially lead to accidents.
